Answer C (I think I'll go with this one):
On a more serious vein, I see I'm dealing with a view that security is =
binary.=20
That one can only be safe in a meaningful sence, when one has three lap=
tops in=20
a particular setup on their desk.

Problem is, people DIE, NOW, because they use Skype. Not because they=20=

misjudged a particular way software A uses crypto primitive B or some s=
uch,=20
but because they are using an inherently fucked up, security wise, soft=
ware to=20
communicate.

Those people do not have the privilege of having a desk with 3 laptops,=
 they=20
often don't even have damn ADMIN RIGHTS on their laptop. Giving them a =
tool=20
that works on their (insecure, I agree!!) platforms and yet LOWERS thei=
r=20
exposure actually can save lives.

This is something that has to be rammed into the heads of people with a=
=20
baseball bat. Ideal setups don't exist, that's why they are "ideal".

Here, have a read:
https://medium.com/message/81e5f33a24e1

Especially this part:

=2D - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -=
