in the same way performing an appendectomy on yourself is theoretically=
=20
possible. This one guy did it once in Antarctica, why can=E2=80=99t you=
?

(...)

So the question I put to hackers, cryptographers, security experts,=20
programmers, and so on was this: What=E2=80=99s the best option for peo=
ple who can=E2=80=99t=20
download new software to their machines? The answer was unanimous: noth=
ing.=20
They have no options. They are better off talking in plaintext I was to=
ld, =E2=80=9Cso=20
they don=E2=80=99t have a false sense of security.=E2=80=9D Since they =
don=E2=80=99t have access to=20
better software, I was told, they shouldn=E2=80=99t do anything that mi=
ght upset the=20
people watching them. But, I explained, these are the activists, organi=
zers,=20
and journalists around the world dealing with governments and corporati=
ons and=20
criminals that do real harm, the people in real danger. Then they shoul=
d buy=20
themselves computers, I was told.

That was it, that was the answer: be rich enough to buy your own comput=
er, or=20
literally drop dead. I told people that wasn=E2=80=99t good enough, got=
